  "prompt": "Which one is the best book of Chemistry for 12th ISC?",
  "response": "For 12th ISC Chemistry, one of the most highly recommended books is **\"Chemistry for ISC Class 12\" by Dr. Viraf J. Dalal**. This book is known for its comprehensive coverage of the ISC syllabus, clear explanations, and numerous practice problems. It aligns well with the ISC exam pattern and includes both theoretical and practical aspects of chemistry.\n\nAdditionally, students often find **\"Concise Inorganic Chemistry\" by J.D. Lee** and **\"Organic Chemistry\" by Morrison and Boyd** helpful for deeper understanding and preparation for competitive exams.\n\nIt's always a good idea to supplement your studies with your school's prescribed textbook and to consult with your teacher for specific recommendations tailored to your needs.",
